{"type":"message","id":"a92a641a","parentId":"642d2f30","timestamp":"2026-03-09T21:02:21.018Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Mon 2026-03-09 16:02 CDT] [Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/1). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\n\n[Subagent Task]: Message for Azeem: Tony says he loves the team. Start now on automation reliability: return 5 reliability checks to reduce overnight failures."}],"timestamp":1773090141015}}
{"type":"message","id":"85b3e42e","parentId":"a92a641a","timestamp":"2026-03-09T21:02:24.189Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Message for Azeem: Tony says he loves the team. \n\nRegarding automation reliability, here are 5 reliability checks to reduce overnight failures:\n\n1. Monitor for system resource exhaustion (CPU, memory, disk I/O) to catch performance bottlenecks.\n2. Verify success/failure status of each automation task and ensure proper error handling and retries.\n3. Check log files for unexpected errors or warnings indicating failure points.\n4. Validate external dependencies (network connections, APIs, servers) are reachable and healthy.\n5. Schedule automated test runs for critical flows regularly and alert on deviations/failures.\n\nThese checks aim to catch common issues early and improve stability overnight. Let me know if you want me to elaborate or handle implementation steps.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_04d18166d5d217840069af355da47081a1990d7882bf96e75b\"}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-4.1-mini","usage":{"input":3631,"output":150,"cacheRead":4864,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":8645,"cost":{"input":0.0014524000000000002,"output":0.00024000000000000003,"cacheRead":0.00048640000000000006,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0021788000000000003}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773090141017}}
